# Manipal Jaipur Classroom Q&A Web App

A premium, real-time web application for anonymous classroom Q&A, designed for Manipal Jaipur. Students can ask questions anonymously, upvote/downvote, and join sessions using a class code. Teachers host sessions, view and manage questions, and mark them as answered.

## Features
- Anonymous student question submission
- Upvote/downvote system (one vote per device per question)
- Real-time updates (Socket.io)
- Session/class code system for joining
- Separate student and teacher interfaces
- Premium Manipal Jaipur branding and UI
- Responsive design

## File Structure
- `index.html` — Main web app UI
- `style.css` — Premium Manipal Jaipur theme and styles
- `app.js` — Frontend logic (session, voting, rendering)
- `session-server.js` — Node.js/Express backend (sessions, questions, voting, Socket.io)
- `questions.json` — Stores questions and votes
- `muj.webp` — Manipal Jaipur logo
- `readme` — Project documentation

## Getting Started
1. **Install dependencies:**
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```
2. **Start the server:**
   ```bash
   node session-server.js
   ```
3. **Open `index.html` in your browser.**
   - For real-time features, ensure the backend is running.

## Customization
- Update `style.css` for further UI enhancements.
- Replace `muj.webp` for custom branding.

## Deployment
- Can be run locally or deployed to cloud platforms supporting Node.js (e.g., Heroku, Vercel).

node session-server.js

